<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-05-18T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-05-18T10:00:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/3721: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Houghton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-05-18T16:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">May 18,
                                        1925—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 18—10:58 (?)
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>148. Department’s number 154, dated May 16, 4 p.m. Foreign Office has
                            assured me that it will issue proper instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Houghton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
